# Microsoft Outlook Setup Guide

## Purpose

This guide provides step-by-step instructions for setting up Microsoft Outlook on Windows, macOS, iOS, and Android, ensuring access to work email, calendars, and contacts.

---

## When to Use This Guide

Use this guide when:

- Setting up a new device  
- Reinstalling or reconfiguring Outlook  
- Assisting users who’ve changed their password or email credentials  
- Configuring mobile access for on-the-go use  

---

## Requirements

- Valid work email address (e.g., `firstname.lastname@company.com`)  
- Network password (domain credentials)  
- Stable internet connection  
- *(Optional)* Multi-factor authentication (MFA) device/app  
- **Mobile only**: Outlook app downloaded from App Store or Google Play  

---

## Set Up Outlook on Windows (Office 365 / Exchange)

### Step 1: Open Outlook

- Click **Start** > search for and open **Outlook**  
- If this is the first time, setup will begin automatically  
- If not, go to **File > Add Account**

### Step 2: Enter Email & Password

- Type your **full email address**, then click **Connect**  
- Enter your **network password**  
- If prompted, approve **Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)**

### Step 3: Complete Setup

- Click **Finish** when prompted  
- Outlook will begin syncing your **inbox, calendar, and contacts**  
- You’re ready to use Outlook!

---

## Set Up Outlook on macOS

### Step 1: Open Outlook

- Launch **Outlook for Mac**  
- If prompted, select **Exchange** or **Microsoft 365**  
- If Outlook is already open, go to **Tools > Accounts > + (Add Account)**

### Step 2: Enter Email Address

- Enter your **full email address**, then click **Continue**  
- Sign in with your **network password** and authenticate via MFA if prompted  

### Step 3: Allow Permissions

- Accept any permissions or prompts related to **calendar/contacts sync**  
- Your mailbox will begin syncing.

---

## Set Up Outlook on iPhone/iPad (iOS)

### Step 1: Install the Outlook App

- Open the **App Store**  
- Search for **Microsoft Outlook** and install it  

### Step 2: Add Account

- Open **Outlook**  
- Tap **Add Account**  
- Enter your **work email address**, then tap **Add Account**

### Step 3: Sign In

- Enter your **password** when prompted  
- Approve any **MFA prompt** if required  

### Step 4: Grant Permissions

- Tap **Allow** to sync your **calendar, notifications, and contacts**  
- You’ll now see your **inbox, calendar, and folders**.

---

## Set Up Outlook on Android

### Step 1: Install the Outlook App

- Open the **Google Play Store**  
- Search for and install **Microsoft Outlook**

### Step 2: Add Your Account

- Open **Outlook**  
- Tap **Get Started**, then enter your **email address**

### Step 3: Sign In

- Enter your **password** and approve MFA  
- Tap **Allow** when prompted for permissions  
- ✅ You can now access your work email on your **Android device**.

---

## Test Access After Setup

After setup is complete, verify:

- Emails are **sending/receiving**  
- **Calendar events** are visible and syncing  
- You can **search your mailbox**  
- **Contacts** populate in the Outlook app  

---

## Troubleshooting Tips

| **Issue**                       | **Suggested Fix**                                         |
|----------------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
| Login fails or email won't sync | Verify credentials, reset password, ensure internet       |
| MFA prompt doesn’t appear       | Check MFA app settings or re-register device              |
| Calendar not syncing on mobile  | Reinstall Outlook, re-enable sync permissions             |
| Duplicate account warning       | Remove and re-add account via Outlook settings            |
| App crashes or lags             | Update Outlook and device OS to latest versions           |

---
